sequenceDiagram
    participant User as "User"
    participant Backend as "Backend"
    participant Database as "Database"

    note "Phone Swap Request Feature"
    note "Date: October 14, 2025"

    User->>Backend: POST /api/phone-swaps (Request Phone Swap)
    note "Form submission with phone to request and phone to exchange fields"
    Backend->>Database: Create new swap request in database
    Database->>Backend: Confirm creation of new swap request

    note "Backend validation: ensure user is owner of offered phone"

    Backend->>User: Confirmation message (Phone Swap Request Successful)
    User->>Backend: GET /api/phone-swaps (Check status of swap request)

    note "Swap request status updates in database"
    Database->>Backend: Update swap request status to 'Pending'
    Backend->>User: Notification (Swap Request Pending)

    loop 10 times
        User->>Backend: GET /api/phone-swaps (Check status of swap request)
        Backend->>Database: Check swap request status in database
        Database->>Backend: Update swap request status to 'Approved' or 'Rejected'
        Backend->>User: Notification (Swap Request Approved/Rejected)
    end

    note "Phone Swap Request Feature implementation details"
    note "Frontend: add 'Request Phone Swap' button, modal form with dropdown lists and text area"
    note "Backend: create new API endpoint for phone swap requests, database schema for swap requests"

content:
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as "User"
    participant Frontend as "Frontend"
    participant Backend as "Backend"
    participant Database as "Database"

    note "Phone Swap Request Feature"
    note "Date: October 14, 2025"

    User->>Frontend: Click "Request Phone Swap" button
    Frontend->>Modal: Trigger modal pop-up
    Modal->>User: Display form with fields:
        Phone to Request: Dropdown list of available phones
        Phone to Exchange: Dropdown list of user's owned phones
        Reason for Request (Optional): Text area for comments
        Actions: "Submit Request" and "Cancel" buttons

    User->>Modal: Fill out form and submit request
    Modal->>Frontend: Send form data to Frontend
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/phone-swaps with form data
    Backend->>Database: Store swap request in database table
        |+ Columns:
            |- Requester's ID
            |- Requested phone
            |- Offered phone
            |- Status (defaulting to 'Pending')
            |- Comment

    Backend->>Frontend: Validate user ownership of offered phone
    Frontend->>User: Display confirmation message upon successful submission
    User->>Frontend: Close modal pop-up

    note "Action Items"
    UX Team: Create wireframe of modal and form by EOD, October 17
    Backend Team: Develop new API endpoint and database schema. Target completion: October 21
    Frontend Team: Build "Request Phone Swap" button and basic modal structure. Begin implementation once wireframes are approved
    Product Manager: Create formal Jira ticket with defined user story and acceptance criteria

    note "Entities"
    - UserDto (class)
    - WeatherForecast (class)
    - UsersController (class)
    - WeatherForecastController (class)
    - IUserService (class)
    - UserService (class)
    - IMongoDBSettings (class)
    - MongoDBSettings (class)
    - AppRoutingModule (class)
    - AppComponent (class)
